      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: correct loopback address detection across multiple subsystems",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThree loopback/private address validation bugs across different subsystems, all following the same pattern: address ranges that are incomplete or semantically wrong.\n\n1. **diffs `isLoopbackClientIp`**: Only matches exact `127.0.0.1`, missing the full 127.0.0.0/8 loopback range. Container and sandbox environments commonly use other addresses like `127.0.0.2`.\n\n2. **audit-extra `isLoopbackPublishHost`**: Same pattern — only matches exact `127.0.0.1` instead of the full 127.0.0.0/8 range.\n\n3. **device-pair `isLoopbackHost`**: Treats `0.0.0.0` (INADDR_ANY — bind to all interfaces) and `::` (IPv6 unspecified) as loopback. These are NOT loopback addresses. The canonical implementation in `src/gateway/net.ts` explicitly excludes both.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nEach fix is minimal (1-2 lines) and follows the established patterns from the canonical implementations in `src/gateway/net.ts` and `packages/net-policy/src/ip.ts`.\n\n**Intentionally NOT changed:**\n- `model-auth isLocalBaseUrl()`: `0.0.0.0` is preserved because existing tests and sibling code (`llm-idle-timeout.ts`) treat it as a local provider endpoint for synthetic local auth. This is an established contract.\n- `session-manager` loop bounds: The `<=` in `buildIndex()` and `getPersistedFileEntries()` is intentional — `rememberLeafControl()` anchors opaque records at `fileEntries.length`, and the tail pass is required to read them back.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- **diffs tests**: 10 test files, 135 tests all pass\n- **audit-extra tests**: 6/6 pass (including `isLoopbackPublishHost` coverage)\n- **net.test.ts `isLoopbackHost`**: 49 test cases pass, explicitly verifying `0.0.0.0` and `::` are NOT loopback in the canonical implementation\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
